page.title: 07Greenland Dock
page.content: Greenland Dock is a old whaling dock .the Inner London Education Authority have turned it into a water sport centre.There are water sports for school children.30 schools use it which means that 750 children use it a week. There are 44 sailing boats The types boats there are pacers,toppers, and wayfarers.There are also 100 canoes. People fish in Greenland Dock becuse they like it there and they can catch lots of fish.They can catch eels, sticktbacks,perch, pine and a trout, carp, roach, dace, rudd and when we went there it was good. And exciting. Our school goes to Greenland dock and they do sail there.Greenland dock looks very good There is a centre there and there are lots of boats. People fish in Greenland dock and catch lots of fish.
